*AWS Site-to-Site VPN*
Connectivity Type	Encrypted IPsec tunnel over the public internet
Quick (hours to a few days)	
Bandwidth limited by internet connection; latency varies
Dependent on internet stability
Encrypted tunnel (IPsec)	
Lower cost, pay for data transfer	
Small/medium workloads, quick hybrid setup, DR connectivity	

*Direct Connect*
Dedicated private fiber link between your data center and AWS
Longer (weeks to months, requires telecom provider)
High bandwidth (1–100 Gbps); consistent low latency
Very reliable, SLA-backed
Private link (no internet exposure); can combine with VPN for encryption
Higher cost (port charges + cross-connect fees)
Enterprise workloads, real-time apps, large data transfers, compliance needs
